article.description: — Noah Horchler had a season-high 20 points as Providence defeated Xavier 83-68 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Horchler scores 20 to carry Providence over Xavier 83-68
article.linkText: Horchler scores 20 to carry Providence over Xavier 83-68
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. -- — Noah Horchler had a season-high 20 points as Providence defeated Xavier 83-68 on Wednesday night. David Duke had 18 points, nine rebounds and nine assists for Providence (12-11, 8-9 Big East Conference). A.J. Reeves added 16 points. Nate Watson had 15 points. Zach Freemantle had 24 points and 12 rebounds for the Musketeers (12-5, 5-5). Paul Scruggs added 22 points. Dwon Odom had 11 points. The Friars leveled the season series against the Musketeers. Xavier defeated Providence 74-73 on Jan. 10. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
